creator: L. Frank Baum
description:
LibriVox recording of The Marvelous Land of Oz (Dramatic Reading) by L. Frank Baum.

Read in English
The Marvelous Land of Oz Being an account of the further adventures of the Scarecrow and Tin Woodman and also the strange experiences of the highly magnified Woggle-Bug, Jack Pumpkin-head, the Animated Saw-Horse and the Gump; the story being A Sequel to The Wizard of Oz. (Summary by L. Frank Baum)

Cast:
Narrator: Bob Neufeld
Tip, Ozma: Charlotte Duckett
Mombi: Shauna Kennett
Jack Pumpkinhead: Jeff K.
Saw-Horse, Sad-Looking Man: Frances Brown
Ferryman: Andy Cotterly
Guardian of the Gates: Matthew Walker
Soldier with the Green Whiskers: nomorejeffs
Scarecrow: tovarisch
Jellia Jamb, Army of Girls, Townsperson: TriciaG
General Jinjur: Elizabeth Klett
Winkie Man: David Olson
Tin Woodman: drakaunus
Mr. Woggle-Bug: Beth Thomas
Queen of the Mice: thestorygirl
Gump: Elliot Gage
Captain, Townsperson: gloriousjob
Glinda: Amanda Friday
Girl of the Army: Elli
Guard of the Army of Girls: Victoria P

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (129MB)

title: The Marvelous Land of Oz (Dramatic Reading)

reviews.reviewbody: Didn't enjoy the book as much as the The Wonderful Wizard Of Oz.  Neither the story nor the characters were as interesting to me.  Why should I care that the "rightful" person rule Emerald City‽  If I lived in Emerald City, I'd tell all perspective rulers to take a flying leap!  Glad that Baum created so many fresh characters for the sequel, while bringing back some old favorites, too.  But I wish I could have liked them all better.  The librivox readers all do a stellar job, such that they earn 5 stars from me even if the book was not perfect.
reviews.reviewtitle: 3 stars for the book itself but 5 stars for the reading

reviews.reviewbody:
Josh in Arizona! Bisbee that is ...and we are just about as odd and diverse as Oz ever hoped to be...and that's why I can say that I agree with Richard..who cares who Rules Oz, as long as it's happy ...however the new characters were fun, as I am sure all Frank's creations will be. 

The readers did an excellent job!!! I look forward to reading myself. As I'm just filling out my volunteer sheet now.
